description._content: Gottlieb, William P., 1917-, photographer. [Portrait of Ray McKinley, (Robert) Dean Kincaide, Bill Ainsworth, Ray Beller, and Peanuts Hucko, Hotel Commodore, Century Room, New York, N.Y., ca. Jan. 1947] 1 negative : b&w ; 2 1/4 x 2 1/4 in. Caption from Down Beat: (center) Leader McKinley and Dean Kincaide Notes: Gottlieb Collection Assignment No. 219 Purchase William P. Gottlieb Forms part of: William P. Gottlieb Collection (Library of Congress). In: "McKinley ork plays most interesting dance music in biz," Down Beat, v. 16, no. 3 (Jan. 29, 1947), p. 8. Subjects: McKinley, Ray Kincaide, (Robert) Dean Ainsworth, Bill Beller, Ray Hucko, Peanuts Ray McKinley Orchestra Jazz musicians--1940-1950. Big bands--1940-1950. Percussionists--1940-1950. Saxophonists--1940-1950. Hotel Commodore Format: Portrait photographs--1940-1950. Cityscape photographs--1940-1950. Film negatives--1940-1950.
